SD=Branch Currency Management
CR=Branch Cash Allocation
BQs= InventoryAllocation
This service domain is responsible for tracking the available cash (currency) inventory held and distributed within the Branch location to teller and ATM positions, to ensure adequate float is always available at all positions. Also to check balances and see that excess cash is transferred to secure central storage as appropriate. If necessary specific criteria can be selected to refine the allocation
The branch management reviews the available float and confirms end of day balances at the teller positions
Track cash inventory, project demand and ensure all cash is accounted for within the branch
CR - Branch Cash Allocation						BQ - Inventory Allocation					
In	Up	Co	Ec	Ca	Re	In	Up	Co	Ec	Ca	Re
InCR Instantiate a new Branch Cash Allocation
UpCR Update details relating to Branch Cash Allocation
CoCR Control the processing of Branch Cash Allocation
EcCR Accept, verify, etc. aspects of Branch Cash Allocation processing
CaCR Capture Branch Cash Allocation activity or event related information
ReCR Retrieve details about any aspect of Branch Cash Allocation
InBQ Instantiate a new Inventory Allocation
UpBQ Update details relating to Inventory Allocation
CoBQ Control the processing of Inventory Allocation
EcBQ Accept, verify, etc. aspects of Inventory Allocation processing
CaBQ Capture Inventory Allocation activity or event related information
ReBQ Retrieve details about any aspect of Inventory Allocation